      "author": "github-actions[bot]",
      "description": "## Summary\r\n\r\n**Version bump:** 1.2.0 → 1.3.0 (minor)\r\n\r\n### New Features\r\n- **Inline Edit Popup**: VS Code-style floating input that appears above selected text. Users type edit instructions, choose append/replace mode, and Copilot streams the result directly into the document. Triggered via command palette (\"Inline edit\") or custom hotkey.\r\n- **Send to Copilot Chat**: Right-click context menu option that sends highlighted text as context to the chat sidebar. Selection appears as a dismissible chip above the input, and is injected into the prompt when the user sends their message.\r\n\r\n### Bug Fixes\r\n- **Chat duplicate bubble fix**: Fixed stacking `assistant.message_delta` handlers on reused sessions causing responses to appear in both current and previous message bubbles. Now uses a delegation pattern with a single registered handler per session.\r\n- **Chat input layout**: Restructured input container with proper flex layout so the Send button stretches to match textarea height.\r\n\r\n### Documentation\r\n- Updated CLAUDE.md with new source file descriptions and architectural patterns\r\n- Updated README.md with feature descriptions and usage instructions for Inline Edit and Send to Chat",
